---
description: Do not wrap function calls across lines just because an argument string is long
alwaysApply: true
---

# No Wrapping Calls for Long Strings

If a function call would wrap only because a string argument is long, extract the string into a variable first.

```python
# BAD
await logger.log(
    "Neighbor timeout reached but waiting for buffered results to drain."
)

# GOOD
msg = "Neighbor timeout reached but waiting for buffered results to drain."
await logger.log(msg)
```
